Agile Principles
1.	To satisfy the customer through consistent and early delivery of the software.
2.	To be able to be flexible with changing requirements, even late into development.
3. To consistently deliver the software to the developer.
4.	For the business side and the development side of the teams to consistently communicate about the project.
5.
To build trust around your team members and to have them motivated.
6.	To communicate face to face with your team members to communicate effectively.
7.	The progress is measured by whether the software is working.
8.	It promotes a sustainable environment, allowing the team to maintain a consistent pace indefinitely.
9.	To have continuous attention to technical excellence and good design, which enhances agility.
10.	And to maximize the amount of work that does not need to be completed.
11.	To allow best architecture, requirements, and design to emerge naturally as the team self-organizes.
12.	At regular intervals the team reflects on how to become more effective, which in turns adjusts their behavior accordingly.


